ce:section.ce:para:
In this study, six kinds of novel CQDs have been developed from herbs. Interestingly, among these CQDs, only the CQDs derived from the proportional mixing of five kinds of herbs could against gram-positive bacteria (S. aureus and MRSA) compared to other five kinds of CQDs derived from individual herbs. Therefore, we focused on this effective CQDs for further experiments (Unless otherwise specified, the CQDs in this article represent this effective CQDs). In addition to the good ABTS radicals scavenging ability, the CQDs can serve as a SOD mimic to catalyze the dismutation of •O2
                     − to H2O2 while they could mimic catalase for catalyzing the decomposition of the producing H2O2 to water and O2. We further proposed a simple strategy to prepare a kind of injectable hydrogel dressing with self-healing ability via a Schiff base linkage between OSA and CMCS, which is decorated with the multifunctional CQDs. The CQDs/hydrogel dressings have rapid self-healing property and good injectability while the hydrogel can continuously release multifunctional CQDs for better wounds management (Scheme 1
                     ). Finally, the therapeutic effect of CQDs/hydrogel on the full-thickness skin defect model with MRSA infection was studied by observing the wound healing process and histological analysis.
